name: Taha Abdulkareem
text:
The name makes it seem as if it is a well established, central location for the community and their Islamic programs. However, they clearly need a qualified scholar to lead them and make the center more Muslim friendly and Islamic. They have one restroom and it doesn't have a bucket for istinjaa. The jumu'a khutba isn't well prepared, or spiritually motivating, or delivered professionally. Words like "Allah" and "shayateen" weren't pronounced correctly by the khateeb. Not a single verse of the Qur'an was recited correctly. And to top it off, men and women prayed in the same small, congested room, without a partition (which is wrong and unIslamic, regardless of what anyone says).

May Allah give us all guidance and allow us to find those who have the correct understanding of Islam, benefit from them, and pass on the knowledge and practice to others. آمين

Definitely not worth a visit....at all.....

text: Wonderful masjid and community.  The doors are open and it's a very well thriving masjid and community. The 5 prayers are daily at the masjid... the brothers side is always open. There is Sunday School for the kids August - May. There's a Monthly dinner and a Fun Day for the kids every so often. 3id salaah, and celebrations. The community is close and very nice. We welcome all, and happy to have anyone looking for a place to worship stop by and those looking to learn more about Islam come visit.
